id: harness-mandatory-policy
severity: critical
description: "Agent bootstrap is mandatory on every spawn. The bootstrap harness is the ONLY authorized entry point."
guard: "NO AGENT MAY PERFORM ANY WORK WITHOUT RUNNING THE BOOTSTRAP HARNESS FIRST. The bootstrap script is the ONE harness for all agents. It authenticates, registers, and validates before any agent action."
rules:
  - agent-bootstrap.sh MUST run as FIRST command on EVERY agent spawn
  - Session is registered with identity: name, type, version, session ID, host, PID, start time
  - If bootstrap fails, agent is NOT AUTHORIZED to work
  - No other bootstrap or harness script is allowed
  - Bootstrap must run before any code, deploy, or config change
  - Bootstrap must run before every session, not just first time
